frameDefinitions: A particular Binding_principle is (or is not) operative, that is, any obligations, restrictions, and any other aspects of the Binding_principle are (or are not) in effect.
Due to internal forces/properties, an Entity is inclined towards a particular Behavior, which may be to perform an action or to maintain a state.
An Entity is declared to exist, generally irrespective of its position or even the possibility of its position being specified.
An Entity is evaluated for whether or not it belongs to a particular Reference_category in a context where its category membership is doubtful.

Against the background of a contextually salient non-real world, for instance a hypothetical, imagined, simulated, expected, projected, or dream world, an Instance of a Type encountered in a relation or event in the real world is presented as being different from the instance found in the non-real world.
This frame concerns an Evaluee being judged for its quality, i.e. how much it would probably be liked.
frameExamples: This law will only become in <t>effect</t> during the last three weeks of the year.
Finally, Poland ceased to <t>exist</t> as a state for hundreds of years.

It can be hard to get your money back after discovering you've bought a <t>bogus</t>
autograph for hundreds or thousands of dollars!
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Binding_principle</fen> is the law, contract, principle, or other (set of) obligations that is (or is not) operational.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Binding_principle</fen> is in effect.
The <fen>Place</fen> at which the <fen>Binding_principle</fen> is or is not operational.
TheFrame Element <fen>Entity</fen> identifies the person or thing that has a tendency towards some Behaviour.
Some entity, abstract or concrete, which is stated to exist.
A time at which the entity is in existence.
The <fen>Entity</fen> that is being evaluated in terms of whether it is an instance of the <fen>Reference_category</fen>.
The type relative to which the <fen>Entity</fen> is evaluated.
The real-world individual--a concrete or abstract thing or an event--which differs from its counterpart in a discourse-salient non-real world.
A kind of entity, instances of which are expected to occur in both the real and the non-real world.
The <fen>Evaluee</fen> is being judged for its quality.
listRoleExamples: Once <fex>the treaty</fex> is in effect, US port authorities and the Coast Guard will monitor compliance by checking any yacht 79 feet or longer.
All patent applicants and owners should be aware of the current uncertainty as to what patent fees will be in effect <fex>on October 1, 1998</fex>
This promotion is void <fex>in the state of Florida</fex>.
<fex>Lubomir</fex> was not inclined to believe me
<fex>The bomb found at the US Embassy in Berlin</fex> was fake.
In May of 1994, FBI agents working for Mr. Fiske interviewed Mrs. Foster, showed her <fex>an ACTUAL  gun</fex>, not a photo, and asked her if she could identify the gun.
